FBIS3-43278 "drafr001_e_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Government Says No Retrenchment Exercise AB3112160993 Kaduna Radio Nigeria in English 0900 GMT 31 Dec 93 AB3112160993 Kaduna Radio Nigeria Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The federal government says it will not carry out any retrenchment exercise in the civil service based on the International Monetary Fund recommendations. The minister of labor and productivity, Dr. Samuel Ogbemudia, told newsmen in Lagos that recent newspaper reports on the issue were unfounded. Dr. Ogbemudia said that government's recent pronouncement on industrial action was not upright to the labor movement.
